post_text:
Special Meeting Update
The Livingston County, Kentucky Board of Education is holding a special meeting on August 31, 2020 6:00 PM in the LCHS Gymnasium or Music Room. Public attendance may be limited due to social distancing guidelines. Masks are requested to be worn by the general public. Please maintain 6-feet physical distancing from individuals who are not within your household. 50% maximum capacity.
The meeting will be broadcast for public viewing via Facebook Live at https://www.facebook.com/livingstoncountyschools
The agenda can be found at this link: https://portal.ksba.org/public/Agency.aspx?PublicAgencyID=104&AgencyTypeID=1

Public comments will not be part of this meeting. The primary topic is the same as the last meeting. Individuals are encouraged to continue sharing their insights and desires with their board member representatives. The board members have been doing their research on the issue at hand and three board members have requested to hold this meeting to reconsider the topic of in-person classes.

Livingston County, Kentucky
August 24 at 9:22 AM ·

The fruits and vegetables are here!!

We have started handing out FREE fruits and vegetables and will do so until they are all gone, or 7 P.M. Come on down to the UK Extension Office (old fairgrounds) and get a couple boxes for the family.

We have 1700 boxes to give away, so don't be bashful!. There is a mixture of lots of different things, but so far we are noticing A LOT of jalapenos, so if you like em, come get em. Each box has 4 sealed containers, with a variety of everything.

Again, there is NO INCOME REQUIREMENT. Anybody can take part in this program and come. We have volunteers (thank you to all of them!!) who will load your car up so you don't even have to get out.

If you are wanting some, but transportation is an issue, please call the Judge Executive Office at 270.928.2105, and we'll do our best to help.

post_text: Tomorrow, May 13th will be the last official student attendance day for this school year. Students may continue to return completed work to each school with Monday, May 18th being the last day for submitting completed Live RED at Home packets. Each school is planning end of the year activities and will be sharing those details with their students and families. Tomorrow will also be the last day of meal pickup at all of our mobile sites and for home deliveries. Beginning Monday, May 18th through Monday June 29th, families may pick up meals on Mondays and Wednesdays at North Livingston Elementary and Livingston Central High School between the hours of 10:00 am and 1:00 pm. For more information regarding summer meals you may contact Kristy Nelson, Food Service Director.

post_text: Today in a conference call with superintendents, Governor Andy Beshear recommend that all in-person classes and activities be cancelled for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. Livingston County Schools will continue providing instruction through Live RED at Home Days for the remainder of this school year until the last official day of school. Additional information regarding end-of-the year activities for each school will be communicated in the near future.

post_text: Good afternoon. We hope that everyone is staying healthy and safe. For those families needing copies of the Live RED at Home packets for days 11 through 20, they will be available for pickup tomorrow, Tuesday March 24th from 10:00 am to 1:00 pm at each school. post_text: The contractor responsible for the construction on the Smithland bridge recently presented plans for completing necessary repairs. The final construction plans are much better than originally anticipated. Beginning November 1st, the bridge will be closed between 8 p.m. and 5 a.m. for the work to be completed. The bridge will open to two-lane traffic during the day. Engineers with the Kentucky Transportation Cabinet have confirmed that the bridge is safe for buses to cross during the construction period. This will allow us to safely proceed with our regular school schedule and bus routes. Using the One Call polling feature, the school district contacted affected parents/guardians and asked whether or not they would allow their student(s) to cross the bridge on a school bus. District representatives will continue to communicate and work with those who have concerns as we strive to meet the individual needs of our students. communications@livingston.kyschools.us

Would you rather two-step to country or salsa with mariachi? Students in Livingston County Schools had to opportunity to experience both during Wednesday’s National School Lunch Week! Livingston Central High School students line danced to country music through the cafeteria on their way to try a NEW menu item, BBQ Nachos. Students at South Livingston Elementary, North Livingston Elementary, and Livingston County Middle might have been tempted to wear sombreros while trying another NEW menu item, Create-Your-Own Burrito Bowl, and listening to mariachi music. We are proud of our students for always being up to the challenge of trying new things!

NLES: Hunter Collins, Keagan Ward, Autumn Scales
LCMS: Ryelei Bennett, Adriel Barnes, Kurstin Williams

post_text: Congratulations to Mrs. Vonda Todd for being the Live RED recipient for the month of September. Her nomination reads: Ms. Vonda Todd, with Farmers Bank, was the heart and soul behind our recent Community School Supply Drive. This effort proved to be successful beyond everyone’s expectations except Ms. Vonda’s. She is an exceptional community partner who went above and beyond for our students. She is an extremely positive, passionate person. Because of her efforts, the Community School Supply Drive raised enough supplies and monetary donations to meet the needs of our students. With an attitude of never giving up, she made phone call after phone call, picked up and delivered supplies and more. She was confident that our community would rise to the challenge. Vonda Todd is an extraordinary example of Living RED and we are blessed to have her in our community.

post_text: Family First & Cardinal Connection will host Wet & Wild the last four Wednesday’s in July, which includes the 10th, 17th, 24th and 31st. Students currently enrolled in Livingston County Schools, ages 11 and up, must complete the permission form to ride the bus. Please see your Summer Event Catalogue or Livingston County Schools website for a copy of the permission slip and the bus schedule. Daily passes for these dates will be $15. Others not riding the bus, including small children, are invited to join us at Venture River anytime on the designated days. Families wishing to enter the park at this reduced rate, will need to present a Family First Pass at the gate, and will pay the park directly. These passes were distributed before school dismissed, but are still available at the Livingston County Board of Education Office and the UK Extension Office. All students not riding the bus will be the responsibility of the adult bringing them to the park and no permission form is required. Permission slips are only required for students riding the bus.

post_text: The process for receiving Venture River Passes through Family First & Cardinal Connection has changed, we will have Wet and Wild Wednesdays again this year at Venture River on July 10th, 17th , 24th, and 31st. If your family plans to join us at Venture River this summer, please see Family First or Cardinal Connection at your child's school tomorrow, May 21st or contact one of our offices to receive the Livingston County Family Discount Card which is needed in order to get the discounted rate at the gate. Cards are also available at the Livingston County Board Of Education Office or UK Extension office in Smithland.

post_text:
Family First and Cardinal Connection will partner with Livingston Hospital & Healthcare Services to provide free community physicals on May 31st at Livingston County Middle School. Appointments will be available from 1:00pm-5:00pm. Please contact Family First or Cardinal Connection by May 20th to reserve an appointment slot. Appointments are limited. This is a great opportunity to get your Entry in to Kindergarten, 6th grade or sports physical for free. Call for an appointment.

post_text: All after-school programming concludes on Thursday, April 25th. Morning programming concludes on Friday, May 3rd. Summer sign-up sheets were sent home Friday, April 19th. If interested in attending summer programming, ask for a registration packet for your child.

post_text: The Young Leaders in Action Team from LCMS received recognition at the April Livingston County Board of Education Meeting. These young ladies, Ashley Adams, Hannah Fisher, Trinity Ray and Katelyn Riley, were recognized for their 3rd place finish in the regional competition. Congratulations to these young ladies on setting the example of Living RED.
